<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - INSTALL - SHIFT KNOB
        (ROADRANGER VALVE)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT KNOB (ROADRANGER VALVE)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If necessary, secure the air lines to the shift lever.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the valve cover over the shift lever and air lines, and install the jam nut on the
                shift lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the air fittings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Screw the shift knob onto the shift lever. Position the shift knob so the range shift lever
                faces the front of the vehicle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the jam nut against the bottom of the shift knob to 48 to 61 Nm (35 to 45 ft-lbs) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032h7">Figure 177</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the air lines to the air fittings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the cover into position on the shift knob.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shift knob cover two (2) mounting screws (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032h8">Figure 178</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13032h7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032H7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 177. Tighten Jam Nut</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f13032h8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032H8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 178. Install Shift Knob Cover Mounting Screws</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
